<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-03-01T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-03-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="790" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d790">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102S/1997: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-03-01T19:00:00-05:00">March 1, 1940—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>30. Your 92, February 24, 11 a.m., and Shanghai’s 159, February 26, 2
                                p.m., Shanghai extra-Settlement roads. You are authorized <pb facs="0742" n="734" xml:id="pg_734"/> to reply to the Chinese
                                Foreign Office along the lines of the draft outlined in your
                                telegram under reference, amended as suggested in Shanghai’s 159,
                                February 26, 2 p.m.</p>
                            <p>Sent to Chungking. Repeated to Peiping and Shanghai.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>